

=Definition=

Jon Wilkins:

 
"There are a lot of people out there who have the expertise and the interest to contribute to scholarly research, but for whom, for whatever reason, the seventy-hour-a-week academic lifestyle just doesn't work. We need to develop mechanisms that will allow people to participate in research at ten, twenty, or thirty hours a week, and to get paid for doing it."
(http://jonfwilkins.blogspot.com/2012/05/white-paper-on-fractional-scholarship.html)

